-- PRESS DIGEST- Financial Times - July 18
-- 
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 11:52PM EDT
-- None



July 18 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories in the Financial Times. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

Headlines  GOOGLE SALES JUMP ON NEW AD FORMATS (http://on.ft.com/1yzxmWU)  APPLE ADDS BLACKROCK CO-FOUNDER TO ITS BOARD (http://on.ft.com/Wgw4Ch)  TIME WARNER RISES ON HOPES OF HIGHER BID (http://on.ft.com/WlM3z7)  UK BANKS TO FACE FULL INDUSTRY INQUIRY (http://on.ft.com/1nRnAM5)  ROYAL BANK OF SCOTLAND EYES SALE OF COUTTS' OVERSEAS ARM (http://on.ft.com/1oPcljW)  Overview  Google's <GOOGL.O> net revenues rose 25 percent during the second quarter, driven by new forms of product-related search advertising. However higher operating costs left its earnings below Wall Street expectations.  Sue Wagner, a co-founder of the world's biggest money manager BlackRock <BLK.N>, has been appointed to Apple's <AAPL.O> board, becoming the company's second female director as part of a push for greater diversity by Chief Executive Tim Cook.   Time Warner <TWX.N> shares rose further above Twenty-First Century Fox's <FOXA.O> $80 billion offer on Thursday as analysts calculated that Rupert Murdoch's television and film empire could raise the bid that the media group behind HBO and Warner Bros rebuffed.  British Competition and Markets Authority is set to recommend a full-blown inquiry on Friday into small business lending and current accounts.